Arithmeticae opuscula duo, 1507
Dietrich Tzwyvel or Theodoricus Tzwyvel (1490–1536) was a German mathematician, typographer and composer.[1]

Life[edit]
Tzwyvel designed the astronomical clock of the Münster Cathedral.[2]

Works[edit]
Tzwyvel, Theodoricus (1507). Arithmeticae opuscula duo (in Latin). Köln: Heinrich Quentel.
